						<span class="fn">amonshiz</span> <span class="says">said</span> on <a href="/2013/12/code-computer-science/#comment-3188"><time pubdate datetime="2013-12-23T18:19:41-08:00">December 23, 2013 at 6:19 pm</time></a>:					</p><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
	
						
				</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->
	
				<div class="comment-content span7">
					<p>I would argue that engineering or other applied science degrees fit this criteria. It is the process of learning to learn that is gained from a quality BS degree. CS provides some quality instruction specific to the field, but knowing how to learn and find the sources to learn from is the most important part.</p>
